phase2.explanation:
You can't just print a parameter pack directly like that!

**The fix (recursion):**
```cpp
template <typename T, typename... Args>
void print(T first, Args... args) {
    std::cout << first;
    if (sizeof...(args) > 0) std::cout << ", ";
    print(args...);
}

void print() {}  // Base case
```

**The fix (fold expression, C++17):**
```cpp
template <typename... Args>
void print(Args... args) {
    (std::cout << ... << args) << std::endl;
}
```

**PlusPlus-chan says:**
"Parameter packs need expansion. Use recursion or fold expressions."

